The paper deals with natural language understanding and visual reasoning in 3D-rendered scenes, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel module architecture for neural networks, which is a topic that is often studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO).
